<section class="section" aria-labelledby="creator-title">
  <div class="container stack">
    <div class="measure">
      <h2 class="section-title" id="creator-title">Who created this Brazil travel guide?</h2>
      <p class="section-note">
        Brazil Decoded was created by a Brazilian who has lived daily life in the country
        and understands how Brazil is experienced by visitors from abroad.
      </p>
      <p class="section-note">
        After seeing how often tourists arrive with incomplete or misleading information,
        this project was designed to bridge the gap between what tourists expect
        and how Brazil actually works.
      </p>
      <p class="section-note">
        The goal is simple:
        help travelers make better decisions before and during their trip.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" aria-labelledby="purpose-title">
  <div class="container stack">
    <div class="measure">
      <h2 class="section-title" id="purpose-title">Why this Brazil travel guide exists</h2>
      <p class="section-note">
        Most information about Brazil online focuses either on extremes —
        overly optimistic travel marketing or exaggerated fear-based narratives.
      </p>
      <p class="section-note">
        Both approaches fail to prepare travelers for real situations.
      </p>
      <p class="section-note">
        Brazil Decoded was created to focus on:
      </p>
      <ul class="mini-list">
        <li>everyday behavior</li>
        <li>practical safety habits</li>
        <li>cultural expectations</li>
        <li>simple rules locals follow naturally</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="section-note">
        This guide does not try to sell an image of Brazil.
        It explains how to move through the country calmly and confidently.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" aria-labelledby="experience-title">
  <div class="container stack">
    <div class="measure">
      <h2 class="section-title" id="experience-title">Based on real daily life in Brazil</h2>
      <p class="section-note">
        The content in Brazil Decoded is based on lived experience,
        not recycled blog posts or generic travel advice.
      </p>
      <p class="section-note">
        It reflects:
      </p>
      <ul class="mini-list">
        <li>how people actually interact</li>
        <li>how money and transport are handled daily</li>
        <li>what draws attention — and what doesn't</li>
        <li>how tourists are usually perceived</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="section-note">
        The focus is always on practical understanding, not theory.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" aria-labelledby="audience-title">
  <div class="container stack">
    <div class="measure">
      <h2 class="section-title" id="audience-title">Who this Brazil travel guide is for</h2>
      <p class="section-note">
        Brazil Decoded was created especially for:
      </p>
      <ul class="mini-list">
        <li>first-time visitors to Brazil</li>
        <li>travelers who want clear, realistic guidance</li>
        <li>people who prefer understanding rules over guessing</li>
        <li>tourists who value calm, respectful travel</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="section-note">
        This project is not about nightlife, party culture, or luxury travel.
        It's about feeling prepared and confident in everyday situations.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" aria-labelledby="content-creation-title">
  <div class="container stack">
    <div class="measure">
      <h2 class="section-title" id="content-creation-title">How the content is created</h2>
      <p class="section-note">
        All content is written with foreign visitors in mind and follows three principles:
      </p>
      <ul class="mini-list">
        <li><strong>Clarity</strong> – Simple English, no jargon</li>
        <li><strong>Relevance</strong> – Only what truly affects your trip</li>
        <li><strong>Calm guidance</strong> – No fear-based language</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="section-note">
        The guide is reviewed and updated as travel conditions and habits change.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

